Description: Neck and shoulder sherd of Milesian Fikellura (?) pottery oinochoe; traces of white slip; exterior: reserved save for trace of dot rosette; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Joins British Museum 1886,0401.504, 685, 775 and 776. A smaller jug than 1886,0401.774, but similar in other respects.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXII, no. 6)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 717, no. 759)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.103)
